    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The plan for `vim.pos` and `vim.range` has been mostly implemented (big thanks to @ofseed @TheLeoP ). https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/25509 https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/38561\n\nThis tracks remaining work. See subissues also.\n- [ ] TODO: do we need these fields?\n  ```\n  -- row_offset?: number\n  -- col_offset?: number\n  -- vcol?: number  -- virtual column\n  -- vrow?: number  -- virtual row\n  ```\n- [ ] Do we need a `kind` field?\n  ```\n  vim.pos.Pos: {\n    kind?: 'mark' | 'extmark' | 'cursor' | ...\n  }\n  ```\n- [x] Test coverage could be stronger for the `to_inclusive_pos` logic and edge cases.\n- [ ] `Range.has` semantics: Tests only cover one case (`vim.range(0,0,0,4):has(vim.range(0,0,0,0))`). More edge cases would be valuable.\n- [ ] `Range.to_extmark/to_cursor` create temporary `vim.Pos` objects. This partially defeats the performance motivation?\n- [ ]  docs: [callout integer indexing]\n- [ ] support `opts.win=0` to mean \"current win\"?\n- [ ] Refactor old code to use `vim.pos` / `vim.range` \n     - [ ] [compare_position (vscode-neovim)](https://github.com/vscode-neovim/vscode-neovim/pull/1490/files#diff-356c71d28d1ad83654bec96ec39481938dd06e6589a05d781ed2ab028d9296b6R70-R84)\n     - [ ] ?",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Sorry if this is noise but the docs could use some love, especially some examples would be nice. E.g. I would expect that `vim.pos.cursor()` will simply result in a `vim.pos.Pos` object that represents the current cursor position (like `getpos('.')`), but I can't even understand how to correctly call `vim.pos.cursor(...)` (probably a skill issue on my end tho)",
